                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "These include the Golgi apparatus and the nucleolus.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 50,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ1",
                "loop": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We have described structures that change during mitosis. Do any structures stay te same?",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 51,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ2",
                "loop": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We find a set of structures that remain relatively unchanged during mitosis. They all localize to the apical cell-cell contacts.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 52,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ3",
                "loop": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Lets take a closer look at one of these structures, tight junctions.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 53,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ4",
                "loop": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Lets take a closer look at one of these structures, tight junctions.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 54,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ5",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Tight junction protein ZO-1 localizes to apical cell-cell contacts thus highlighting the interfaces between cells within a colony.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 55,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ6",
                "loop": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Tight junctions remain localized at apical cell-cell contacts even as cells undergo massive changes in shape during mitosis.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 56,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ7",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This highlights the importance of maintaining the integrity of the epithelial sheet and its barrier function.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 57,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ8",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Proteins can have multiple localization patterns. Some of those patterns are maintained through mitosis while others may change.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 58,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ9",
                "loop": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Proteins can have multiple localization patterns. Some of those patterns are maintained through mitosis while others may change.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 59,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
